{"name": "pppc", "metadata": {"name": "pppc", "version": "0.1.1", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Games/Entertainment"], "home_page": "https://github.com/retrotee/pppc", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["javabridge", "PyYAML", "typing-extensions", "dataclasses", "jinja2", "black", "isort"], "summary": "Create Minecraft Paper plugins using Python", "upload_time": 1734455459}, "documentation": ["# PPPC (PythonPaperPluginCompiler)\r\n\r\n> \u26a0\ufe0f **BETA WARNING**: This project is currently in active development and beta phase. APIs may change without notice, and some features might be incomplete or unstable. Use in production environments at your own risk.\r\n\r\nPPPC is a Python module that allows you to create Minecraft Paper plugins using Python syntax. It's designed to be beginner-friendly while providing powerful functionality for creating Minecraft server plugins.\r\n\r\n## Development Status\r\n\r\n- \ud83d\udea7 **Beta Phase**\r\n- \u26a0\ufe0f Breaking changes may occur\r\n- \ud83d\udcdd Documentation is being actively developed\r\n- \ud83d\udc1b Bug reports and feedback are welcome\r\n- \ud83e\udd1d Contributions are encouraged\r\n\r\n## Features\r\n\r\n- Python-like syntax for creating Minecraft Paper plugins\r\n- No Java knowledge required\r\n- Support for multiple Bukkit API versions\r\n- Easy event handling and command creation\r\n- Automatic compilation to JAR files\r\n\r\n## Quick Start\r\n\r\n```python\r\nfrom pppc import Plugin, Event, event_handler, command\r\n\r\n# Create a plugin\r\nplugin = Plugin(\r\n    name=\"MyPlugin\",\r\n    version=\"1.0.0\",\r\n    description=\"My first plugin\",\r\n    author=\"YourName\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n# Handle events\r\n@event_handler(\"PlayerJoinEvent\")\r\ndef on_player_join(event):\r\n    player = event.data[\"player\"]\r\n    player.send_message(\"Welcome!\")\r\n\r\n# Create commands\r\n@command(name=\"hello\", description=\"Says hello\")\r\ndef hello_command(sender, args):\r\n    sender.send_message(\"Hello!\")\r\n\r\n# Compile the plugin\r\nfrom pppc import compile_plugin\r\njar_path = compile_plugin(plugin)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Supported Versions\r\n\r\n- 1.21.3 (default)\r\n- 1.20.4\r\n- 1.19.4\r\n- 1.18.2\r\n- 1.17.1\r\n- 1.16.5\r\n\r\n## Installation\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npip install pppc\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Known Limitations\r\n\r\nDuring the beta phase, please be aware of the following limitations:\r\n\r\n- Some advanced Paper API features might not be fully implemented\r\n- Performance optimizations are ongoing\r\n- Error messages and debugging tools are being improved\r\n- Documentation is being expanded\r\n\r\n## Documentation\r\n\r\nFor detailed documentation and examples, visit the [wiki](https://github.com/yourusername/pppc/wiki).\r\n\r\n## Contributing\r\n\r\nContributions are welcome! Please feel free to submit a Pull Request. During the beta phase, we especially appreciate:\r\n\r\n- Bug reports\r\n- Feature requests\r\n- Documentation improvements\r\n- Test coverage improvements\r\n- Code quality enhancements\r\n\r\n## License\r\n\r\nThis project is licensed under the MIT License - see the LICENSE file for details.\r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pppc.exceptions", "documentation": ["Custom exceptions for PPPC"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "pppc.exceptions.PPPCError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Base exception for PPPC"]}, {"name": "pppc.exceptions.ValidationError", "bases": ["PPPCError"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Raised when validation fails"]}, {"name": "pppc.exceptions.CompilationError", "bases": ["PPPCError"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Raised when compilation fails"]}, {"name": "pppc.exceptions.VersionError", "bases": ["PPPCError"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Raised when version is not supported"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "pppc", "documentation": ["PPPC (PythonPaperPluginCompiler) - Create Minecraft Paper plugins using Python"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "pppc.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "pppc.command", "xref": {"fqname": "pppc.decorators.command", "project": null}}, {"name": "pppc.compile_plugin", "xref": {"fqname": "pppc.compiler.compile_plugin", "project": null}}, {"name": "pppc.DEFAULT_VERSION", "xref": {"fqname": "pppc.version.DEFAULT_VERSION", "project": null}}, {"name": "pppc.Event", "xref": {"fqname": "pppc.core.Event", "project": null}}, {"name": "pppc.event_handler", "xref": {"fqname": "pppc.decorators.event_handler", "project": null}}, {"name": "pppc.Plugin", "xref": {"fqname": "pppc.core.Plugin", "project": null}}, {"name": "pppc.SUPPORTED_VERSIONS", "xref": {"fqname": "pppc.version.SUPPORTED_VERSIONS", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "pppc.core", "documentation": ["Core functionality for PPPC"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "pppc.core.Event", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "pppc.core.Event.name", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pppc.core.Event.data", "type": {"name": "Dict", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "t